## Instructions for you (Claude Code)

- **Before touching infra:** read the relevant prompt under `docs/prod/prompts/` cover-to-cover. They are copy-pasteable and sequential.
- **Before touching tuned knobs:** cross-check against `docs/prod/reference/env-tuned.md` and the "hard-earned lessons" above.
- **Don't re-run dev-rejected experiments** without a structural reason (new hardware, new model, etc.). See the memory seed.
- **Use Agent (subagent_type=Explore)** sparingly — this repo is small and your reads are cheap. Reserve it for multi-file codebase questions.
- **Commit often.** Every stack = its own PR if possible.
- **Don't run `cdk deploy` without approval.** All prod deploys go through CI with manual approval.

Have fun.
